      "issue": "Complex networking bandwidth calculations and routing paths (e.g., '256 LPUs x 90 lanes x 112Gbps/8 x 2 directions = 645TB/s').",
      "suggestion": "Maintain the exact mathematical formulas. Break down the surrounding explanatory sentences into short, sequential Chinese clauses to ensure the logic of the data flow is crystal clear."
    },
    {
      "location": "GTC 2026 Supply Chain Implications (Mid-board Optics section)",
      "issue": "Detailed physical descriptions of hardware layouts (e.g., 'MBOM which then connects to the PCB via a land grid array (LGA) socket').",
      "suggestion": "Ensure precise mechanical and electrical engineering terminology is used. For example, use '平面网格阵列 (LGA) 插座' and '前面板 (faceplate)'."
